## Executive Summary

Global Affairs Canada is a significant humanitarian donor, allocating
over \$111 million across eight regions in 2025, with a strategic focus
on Africa. Its funding has substantially increased over recent years,
expanding geographic reach to 33 recipient countries by 2025,
emphasizing diversification. Canada earmarks approximately 25% of its
total \$5 billion funding to targeted sectors, reflecting a preference
for strategic, earmarked investments. Key recurring beneficiaries
include Lebanon, Bangladesh, and Sudan, indicating sustained regional
priorities. Although Canada’s average transaction size and frequency are
lower than peer donors, there is opportunity for growth. Awareness of
these trends enables fundraisers to align proposals with Canada’s
focused and regionally diversified funding approach.
